# Mailing lists

SPI offers a variety of mailing lists.  A description of each active list is below.   Most SPI mailing lists can be found and subscribed to [here](http://lists.spi-inc.org/).

## Announce list

SPI makes official announcements on this list.  All SPI [members](/membership/) are recommended to be on this list.

   * [Archive](https://archives.spi-inc.org/list/spi-announce/)

## General list

The spi-general list is a public list for general discussion of Software in the Public Interest.   All SPI [members](/membership/) are recommended to be on this list.

   * [Archive](https://archives.spi-inc.org/list/spi-general/)

## Private list

The spi-private list is open to all SPI contributing [members](/membership/). Subscription is done on [members](https://members.spi-inc.org).

   * [Archive](https://archives-private.spi-inc.org/list/spi-private/)

## Projects list

Membership of the spi-projects list comprises project liaisons and others as deemed by the board.

   * [Archive](https://archives-private.spi-inc.org/list/spi-projects/)
